n for its beauty and very rich flora and fauna. It also holds the status of a national park. Lake Skadar and the surrounding area are rich in cultural and historic sites, known for the churches and monasteries on the islands in the lake. The area is also known for its medieval castles and fortified towns such as Zabljak Crnojevica, Obod, and the site of the printing press, which printed the first book in this part of the world in 1494, and the well-known Lesendro etc. In this unique natural reserve, rich in flora and fauna, live a large number of birds, amongst them the pelican. Lake Skadar is one of the world\'s unique bird reserves.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Rafting - River Tara</h2>\r\n<div class=\"block license\">\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/tara-eks-big.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-261 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/tara-eks-e1463520445842.jpg\" width=\"125\" height=\"70\" /></a>River rafting is a popular recreation activity in Montenegro, particularly on the Tara River. Tara Canyon, the route of the Tara River, is the deepest canyon in Montenegro and Europe, at 78 kilometers in length and 1,300 meters at its deepest. The canyon is protected as a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and is a part of Durmitor national park.One popular rafting route, follows an 18 kilometer course starting from Brstnovica, that takes approximately three ours. Other rafting routes allows enthusiasts to follow much of the dramatic Tara River Gorge - Europe\'s deepest gorge - passing near waterfalls, under bridges, near old Roman roads, and of course, through \"white water\" rougher waters for those that enjoy the most exciting of rafting trips.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Hiking</h2>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/hiking-eks-big.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-262 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp