INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("316", "1", "2016-05-18 20:42:57", "2016-05-18 20:42:57", "<p id=\"rent-a-car\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Since most travelers prefer to be in charge of their own time and movement while touring the Boka Bay instead of relying on public transportation, we provide several options for you: <em>rental cars</em>, <em>scooters</em>, <em>bicycles</em> and <em>boat</em>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"less\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">All our vecihles are brand new, well maintained and in excelent condition.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vehicles</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/yaris1-big.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-158 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/yaris1-e1463433430194.jpg\" alt=\"yaris1\" width=\"125\" height=\"60\" /></a>Tianis Rent A Car offers you brand new Toyota Yaris, the best possible choice for a reliable and economic car with maximum comfort. All details and informations about prices are available at <a href=\"/toyota-yaris#rent-a-car\">Toyota Yaris page</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/scooter-big.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-159 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/scooter-e1463433481170.jpg\" width=\"125\" height=\"60\" /></a>Hiring a scooter is also a great way to see the Boka Bay coast. A scooter offers one complete freedom without creating parking problems, and additional benefits of being able to calmly visit all the hidden parts of a Bay.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/bicycle-big.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-160 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/bicycle-e1463433531806.jpg\" width=\"125\" height=\"60\" /></a>\r\n\r\nMore and more visitors of Kotor find out that it\'s not only nicer and healthier to cycle, but in most cases also much faster. A cyclist can travel around without limits and never has parking problems. All our bicycles are very well maintained..\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/boat-big.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-161 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/boat-e1463433582119.jpg\" width=\"125\" height=\"60\" /></a>Kotor is so much more than just the cosy streets of the Old town. Kotor\'s wonderful position on the end of Boka Bay gives unique opportunities for numerous sea based activities. It is possible to hire a boat for a few hours, a day, or as long as you like.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\">We deliver our vehicles anywhere you need in Montenegro. We also offer our driver when renting vans or cars, driver on customer account AP company terms. We can transfer you to desired destinations outside Montenegro such as Croatia or Serbia. We can also wait for your relatives or partners at the airport of Dubrovnik, Tivat or Podgorica and transfer them to the desired destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conditions:</h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Minimum rental is 24 hours.</li>\r\n 	<li>Driver´s experience – driving licence not less then two years. Driver´s age not younger than 22.</li>\r\n 	<li>Car hire payable in advance, cash or with credit cards, Vat included.</li>\r\n 	<li>Car would be rented with full level and returned in the same condition.</li>\r\n 	<li>Border crossing is granted only with written company permission, otherwise is strictly forbidden.</li>\r\n 	<li>Insurance does not cover damages to windscreen, tyres or vehicle bottom.</li>\r\n 	<li>All traffic expences, parking or fees, same as penalities are on customer´s responsibility.</li>\r\n 	<li>Loss of keys or documents will be charged from 500 – 1000 €.</li>\r\n 	<li>Vehicle takeover outside of Kotor is chargeable, starting from 25 km and 1 euro per every km plus.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\nPlease <a href=\"/contact#contact\">contact us</a> for additional details about rental services.", "Vehicles", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "107-revision-v1", "", "", "2016-05-18 20:42:57", "2016-05-18 20:42:57", "", "107", "http://localhost:8000/107-revision-v1", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("318", "1", "2016-05-25 18:52:27", "2016-05-25 18:52:27", "<p style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\">Our travel agency offers private tours, excursions and different programs for travelers to Kotor and Montenegro. These programs can be customized according to individual preferences and provide the opportunity to experience Montenegro in an unforgettable, intimate and personal way.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The tailor made tours can be organized for any number of participants, any time for any route.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Currency</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Montenegrin currency is euro (EUR). 1 EUR = 100 cents.\r\nThe exchange of other foreign currencies is carried out at the counters of business banks and currency exchange offices.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Banks</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The most widespread cards are VISA, Master, Maestro and Diners, so you can carry out all kinds of monetary transactions. Foreign citizens may bring into the country unlimited quantity of foreign currencies in cache which have to be reported on the occasion of entering the country, in order to be able to take them out.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Airports</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have chosen to arrive by air, you could get here by one of the nearby international airports, Tivat or Podgorica, or at international airport Cilipi (Dubrovnik, Croatia) that is only 16 km away from the state border, and less then 60km from Kotor.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Airport Podgorica (TGD)</strong> is located 10km outside Podgorica, capital of Montenegro, and 90km from Kotor approximately 1, 5 hours by car. There are scheduled flights to Belgrade (Serbia) as well as to various European destinations. During summer season there are many charter flights to all major European cities.</p>\r\nPodgorica airport info phone: +382 81 243 007\r\nWeb site: <a href=\"http://www.montenegroairports.com/eng\">www.montenegroairports.com</a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Airport Tivat (TIV)</strong> is an ideal choice for our guests. It is situated less than 10 kilometers from Kotor, and it takes only 10 minutes to get from it tour hotel. There are daily flights to Belgrade (Serbia) as well as to menu European destinations. During summer season there are also charter flights to major cities of Europe.</p>\r\nTivat airport Info phone: +381 82 670 960\r\nWeb site: <a href=\"http://www.montenegroairports.com/eng\">www.montenegroairports.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Airport of Cilipi (Dubrovnik, Croatia)</strong> is 25 kilometers far from Herceg Novi (50km to our hotel) and there is organized transfer by buses to all tourist destinations in Montenegro, including Kotor.\r\n\r\nCilipi airport info phone : +385 20 773 377\r\nWeb site: <a href=\"http://www.airport-dubrovnik.hr/index.php/en/\">www.airport-dubrovnik.hr</a>\r\n\r\nOn personal request of our guests, we could organize transfer from and to the airport (Podgorica, Tivat, and Cilipi - Dubrovnik).\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sea transfer</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are four international ports in Montenegro: Bar, Budva, Kotor and Herceg Novi. Port of Bar is connected with Italy by regular lines Bar-Bari and Bar-Ancona.</p>\r\nPort of Bar info phone: +381 85 243 007\r\nWeb site: <a href=\"http://www.lukabar.me/index.php/en/\">www.lukabar.me</a>\r\n\r\nPort of Kotor info phone: 381 82 325 572\r\nWeb site: <a href=\"http://www.portofkotor.co.me/en\">www.portofkotor.co.me</a>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Car transportation and parking</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Vehicle insurance is mandatory (carried out at the border crossing) , but Montenegro has got a special agreement with most European countries that keep out their citizens from this obligation. There is also a special \"eco\" tax (10€ per vehicle), that has to be paid on the border crossing.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For any kind of information regarding your arrival and accommodation, please don\'t hesitate to <a href=\"/contact#contact\">contact us</a>.</p>", "Tourist Info", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "tourist-info", "", "", "2016-06-04 19:32:46", "2016-06-04 19:32:46", "", "0", "http://localhost:8000/?page_id=318", "0", "page", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("319", "1", "2016-05-25 18:52:27", "2016-05-25 18:52:27", "<h1>The Gulf of Kotor</h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><em>The Gulf of Kotor</em> is surely one of the most beautiful bays in the world. Kotor, old medieval town, lies at the very furthest end of the fjord.</p>\r\n<p class=\"less\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\"Winding, fjordlike inlet of the Adriatic coast, Montenegro. A fine natural harbour, it comprises four bays linked by narrow straits. The stark mountains around the bay slope steeply to a narrow shoreline on which citrus fruits and subtropical plants grow and tourist facilities have been developed\" - Encyclopedia Britannica</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our travel agency offers private tours, excursions and different programs for travellers to Kotor and Montenegro. These programs can be customized according to individual preferences and provide the opportunity to experience Montenegro in an unforgettable, intimate and personal way.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The tailor made tours can be organized for any number of participants, any time for any route.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Currency</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Montenegrin currency is euro (EUR). 1 EUR = 100 cents.\r\nThe exchange of other foreign currencies is carried out at the counters of business banks and currency exchange offices.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Banks</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The most widespread cards are VISA, Master, Maestro and Dineres, so you can carry out all kinds of monetary transactions. Foreign citizens may bring into the country unlimited quantity of foreign currencies in cache which have to be reported on the occasion of entering the country, in order to be able to take them out.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Airports</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have choosed to arrive by air, you could get here by one of the nearby international airports, Tivat or Podgorica, or at international airport Cilipi (Dubrovnik, Croatia) that is only 16 km away from the state border, and less then 60km from Kotor.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Airport Podgorica (TGD)</strong> is located 10km outside Podgorica, capital of Montenegro, and 90km from Kotor aproximaly 1, 5 hours by car. There are scheduled flights to Belgrade (Serbia) as well as to various European destinations. During summer season there are many charter flights to all major European cities.</p>\r\nPodgorica airport info phone: +382 81 243 007\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Airport Tivat (TIV)</strong> is an ideal choice for our guests. It is situated less than 10 kilometers from Kotor, and it takes only 10 miniutes to get from it tour hotel. There are daily flights to Belgrade (Serbia) as well as to menu European destinations. During summer season there are also charter flights to major cities of Europe.</p>\r\nTivat airport Info phone: +381 82 670 960\r\nWeb site: www.aptivat.com\r\n\r\n<strong>Airport of Cilipi (Dubrovnik, Croatia)</strong> is 25 kilometers far from Herceg Novi (50km to our hotel) and there is organized transfer by buses to all tourist destinations in Montenegro, including Kotor.\r\n\r\nCilipi airport info phone : +385 20 773 377\r\nWeb site: www.airport-dubrovnik.hr\r\n\r\nOn personal request of our guests, we could organize transfer from and to the airport (Podgorica, Tivat, and Cilipi - Dubrovnik).\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sea transfer</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are four international ports in Montenegro: Bar, Budva, Kotor and Herceg Novi. Port of Bar is connected with Italy by regular lines Bar-Bari and Bar-Ancona.</p>\r\nPort of Bar info phone: +381 85 243 007\r\nWeb site: www.portofbar.cg.yu\r\n\r\nPort of Kotor info phone: 381 82 325 572\r\nWeb site: www.portofkotor.cg.yu\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Car transportation and parking</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Vehicle insurance is mandatory (carried out at the border crossing) , but Montenegro has got a special agreement with most European countries that keep out their citizens from this obligation. There is also a special \"eco\" tax (10€ per vehicle), that have to be paid on the border crossing.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For any kind of informations regarding your arrival and accomodation, please don\'t hesitate to <a href=\"/contact#contact\">contact us</a>.</p>", "Tourist Info", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "318-revision-v1", "", "", "2016-05-25 18:52:27", "2016-05-25 18:52:27", "", "318", "http://localhost:8000/318-revision-v1", "0", "revision", "", "0");
